# Returns the remaining (un-mowed) portion of a mowing area as a list of
# disjoint pieces. Each piece is a MapArea where:
#   * area      = outer ring (CCW) of the piece
#   * obstacles = holes inside the piece. Holes include both the original
#                 area obstacles AND mowed regions detected from mow_progress
#                 (cells with progress >= 0.3 unioned together).
#
# The caller (e.g. PlanCoverageArea BT node) iterates over `pieces` and
# calls opennav_coverage/ComputeCoveragePath once per piece, treating
# `area` as the bounding polygon and `obstacles` as inner cutouts.
#
# When the area is fully covered (no remaining cells), `pieces` is empty
# and `success` is true.

uint32 area_id

---

bool success
string error
mowgli_interfaces/MapArea[] pieces
